@startuml trips-iteration-8-notification-flow
!theme plain
title Invitation Email Notification -- Cross-Concern Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFFCC

actor Organizer
participant "InvitationService" as IS
participant "Invitation\nAggregate" as INV
participant "TravelParty\nProjection" as TP
database "InvitationRepository" as REPO
participant "Spring\nEventPublisher" as PUB
participant "InvitationEmail\nListener\n(AFTER_COMMIT)" as MAIL
participant "SMTP\n(Mailpit)" as SMTP

== Bestehender Flow: Einzel-Einladung ==

Organizer -> IS : InviteParticipantCommand\n(tripId, email, firstName)
IS -> INV : Invitation.create(\n  tripId, inviteeEmail,\n  inviteeName, tripInfo)
activate INV
INV -> INV : registerEvent(\n  InvitationCreated)

note over INV #FFA500
  **InvitationCreated**
  (Business-Event)
  tenantId, tripId, invitationId,
  inviteeEmail, inviteeFirstName,
  tripName, dates, inviterName
end note

INV --> IS : invitation
deactivate INV

IS -> REPO : save(invitation)
activate REPO
REPO --> IS : saved
deactivate REPO

note over PUB : @TransactionalEventListener\n(phase = AFTER_COMMIT)
PUB -> MAIL : InvitationCreated event

MAIL -> SMTP : Send HTML email\nto inviteeEmail
activate SMTP
SMTP --> MAIL : OK
deactivate SMTP

== Erweiterung Iteration 8: Multi-Member-Benachrichtigung ==

Organizer -> IS : InviteParticipantCommand\n(tripId, email, firstName)
IS -> INV : Invitation.create(...)
activate INV
INV -> INV : registerEvent(\n  InvitationCreated)
INV --> IS : invitation
deactivate INV

IS -> TP : findByTenantId(\n  inviteeTenantId)
activate TP
TP --> IS : travelParty\n(members: [{email, name}, ...])
deactivate TP

IS -> IS : Erstelle\nInvitationNotificationRequested\n(tripInfo + alle Member-Emails)

note over IS #DDA0DD
  **InvitationNotificationRequested**
  (lokales Event, NICHT in common)
  tripName, tripStartDate, tripEndDate,
  inviterFirstName, inviterLastName,
  recipients: [
    {email: "anna@...", firstName: "Anna"},
    {email: "bob@...", firstName: "Bob"}
  ]
end note

IS -> REPO : save(invitation)
activate REPO
REPO --> IS : saved
deactivate REPO

PUB -> MAIL : InvitationNotificationRequested

loop fuer jeden recipient
  MAIL -> SMTP : Send HTML email\nto recipient.email
  activate SMTP
  SMTP --> MAIL : OK
  deactivate SMTP
end

note over MAIL
  **Template**: email/invitation-member (bestehend)
  Personalisiert mit recipient.firstName
  Fire-and-forget (Fehler geloggt, nicht propagiert)
end note

== Architektur-Kontext ==

note across
  **Entscheidung (HS-5)**:
  Email-Versand bleibt im Trips SCS.
  Kein separater Notification-Service.
  Kein neues Event in travelmate-common.
  Kein RabbitMQ-Routing fuer Notifications.

  **Begruendung**: Alle Daten (Trip, Invitation, TravelParty)
  sind lokal im Trips SCS verfuegbar. YAGNI.
end note

@enduml
